<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1323" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1323">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/93.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Vice Consul <persName type="to">Davis</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A. A. Neil and J. L. Burt, American citizens, owning bakery Guadalajara,
                            known as “Cía Galletera Nacional “report that Constitutionalist
                            authorities have imposed forced loan five thousand pesos, and these
                            Americans desire postponement time limit to pay until they can reach
                            Guadalajara by steamer sailing California for Manzanillo September
                            26.</p>
                        <p>Endeavor to secure desired postponement, and in reporting result of your
                            efforts, state briefly facts regarding nature of loan imposed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>